# Make A Company skill factory checklist (new catalog skills)

Use this when adding a **canonical skill ID** (e.g. `read-skills`, `create-email`) that appears in the squad capability matrix and Slack runtime.

## Routing philosophy (keywords vs LLM)

- **Minimize new worker keyword lists** (`containsAny`, long `matchesIntentAliases` branches). They do not scale; every new phrase becomes maintenance debt.
- **Semi-desired LLM path:** `employee-factory` **capability router LLM** (`RouterCapabilityIntentLLM`, structured `tool_intent` in `capability_intent_llm.go`) is the right place for **paraphrase and intent** when Tier-1 explicit names and thin catalog aliases are not enough. Treat **one router LLM call** per eligible turn as a normal cost for **dynamic, scalable routing**—not a failure mode.
- **Orchestrator Tier 1** stays **explicit skill ids only** (`tools.go`); do not smuggle fuzzy synonyms into Tier 1. Fuzzy meaning belongs in the worker router LLM or future Tier-2 orchestrator work—not growing `tools.go` keyword lists.

## 1. Contract source of truth

- Add the skill to **`slack-orchestrator`** `DefaultCapabilityContractV1` in `internal/inbound/capability_contract.go` (`Skills[]` + `EmployeeSkillIDs`). Helpers: `internal/inbound/skill_ids.go` (`DefaultCapabilityContractSkillIDs`) avoid duplicating ID lists in tests.
- Update **`employee-factory`** `internal/skillcontract/skillcontract.go` (`CanonicalDefaultSkillIDs`) in the same PR so worker parity tests keep passing.
- Mirror the same shape in **`makeacompany-ai`** `defaultCapabilityCatalog()` (`backend/internal/app/catalog.go`) and update **`src/data/admin/skills-snapshot.json`** if that snapshot is committed.

## 2. Orchestrator Tier 1 (explicit tool naming / pipelines)

- If users should be able to **name the skill explicitly** (e.g. “read skills”, “read-skills”) or use it in **pipeline steps**, add the skill ID to **`tier1PatternEntries`** in `slack-orchestrator/internal/routing/tools.go` (canonical ids plus legacy `write-*` patterns when applicable). Keep the comment in that file aligned with `Skills[].ID`.
- Tier policy: **`bimross-orchestrator-routing-tiers.mdc`**, **`slack-deterministic-tool-routing-contract.mdc`**.

## 3. Employee-factory runtime

- Register an **`advancedCapabilityRoute`** in `internal/slackbot/skill_routes_table.go` with `SkillID`, `RuntimeTool`, `OwnerHint` (`skill_owner_hint.go`), and `Detect`/`Handle`.
- Add **`capabilityIntent*`** wiring in `capability_mismatch.go` (`capabilityIntentCatalog`) + ensure **`normalizeRouterToolIntent`** / dynamic **`capabilityRouterIntentSchema`** on `Bot` include the new skill ID when the router LLM should recognize the tool.
- **`internal/config/assigned_skills.go`** legacy list for Joanne/Garth when extending defaults.
- Tests: `internal/slackbot` route tests + catalog fixtures in `capability_gate_test.go` (`testDefaultCapabilityCatalog`) + `capability_routes_sync_test.go` (route + `capabilityIntentCatalog` coverage vs `skillcontract`). Run **`scripts/check_skill_surface.sh`** in employee-factory and slack-orchestrator after changes.

## 4. Read vs mutating UX (prefix contract)

- **`read-*`:** execute **immediately** when fired (no Confirm/Cancel for that tool).
- **`create-*`**, **`update-*`**, **`delete-*`:** default **Confirm/Cancel** (or established write-stack pattern) before side effects.

Details: **`bimross-slack-skill-read-create-pattern.mdc`**.

## Skill chaining

- Orchestrator **`PipelineStep`** / **`Decision`** (`slack-orchestrator/internal/routing/pipeline.go`, `decide.go`); worker mirror `orchestratorevent.PipelineStep` (`employee-factory/internal/orchestratorevent/v1.go`); **`pipelinectx`** await (`employee-factory/internal/pipelinectx/pipelinectx.go`). Keep pipeline **tool_id** values aligned with canonical skill IDs.

## 5. Docs

- **`employee-factory/docs/skill-runtime-architecture.md`** — file layout, orchestrator split, and **routing philosophy** (minimal keywords, capability router LLM).
- Prefer **catalog copy + router LLM** over expanding substring gates. Remaining NL gates are **phased debt**.

